08335nam a22008295i 9780776627564DE-B159720240306124542.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20182018xxc    fo  d z      eng d  a97807766275647 a10.1515/97807766275642doi  a(DE-B1597)668140  a(OCoLC)1088951902  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  axxccCA 7aPSY0300002bisacsh04a615.8/22qOCoLC223/eng/2023021600aTouch in the Helping Professions :bResearch, Practice and Ethics /ced. by Martin Rovers, Manal Guirguis-Younger, Judith Malette. 1aOttawa : bUniversity of Ottawa Press, c[2018] 4c©2018  a1 online resource (268 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aHealth and Society00tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tAcknowledgements -- tINTRODUCTION Exploring Touch -- tPART I THE THEORY OF TOUCH -- tCHAPTER I Touch Deprivation and Counselling as Healing Touch -- tCHAPTER II Thinking About Touch -- tCHAPTER III Contributions of Sensory Anthropology and Durand's Anthropology to the Symbolic Study of Touch and the Understanding of Boundaries in Psychotherapy -- tChapter IV Healing and the Forbidden Touch: A Reflection on Selected Scripture Stories -- tPART II THE PRACTICE OF TOUCH IN PSYCHOTHERAPY -- tCHAPTER V The Intervention of Touch in Psychotherapy and Trauma Treatment -- tCHAPTER VI A Puppy's Touch: Destressing with Dogs in a University Environment -- tCHAPTER VII Inter-Partner Touch in Couple Counselling: Theory and Emerging Practice -- tPART III THE PRACTICE OF TOUCH IN A SPECTRUM OF PRACTICE -- tCHAPTER VIII The Practice of the Laying on of Hands in Islamic Spiritual Care -- tChapter IX An Angel in My Pocket: Touch, Sacred Objects, and Spiritual Coping -- tChapter X Touch(ed) in Palliative Care Nursing: Moving with/in An Uncertain Practice -- tChapter XI Touch in Supervision -- tPART IV THE ETHICS OF TOUCH IN THE HELPING RELATIONSHIPS AND CONCLUSION -- tCHAPTER XII The Ethics of Touch in the Helping Relationships -- tCONCLUSION Issues of Touch: An Overall View and Integration -- tContributors0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aTouch may well be one of the least understood or talked about subjects in the helping professions. A discussion on the importance and ethics of positive, caring, and appropriate touch in professions such as teaching, nursing and counselling is long overdue. Touch in the Helping Professions delivers just that, weaving together scholarly evidence, research and clinical practice from a wide range of perspectives encompassing philosophy, theology, psychology, and anthropology to challenge assumptions about the role of touch in the helping professions.  The contributors to the volume focus not only on the overarching roles of gender, age, culture and life experience, but go beyond to encompass canine-assisted therapy, touch deprivation, sacred objects, as well as key ethical considerations. The prevailing lack of dialogue, due to fear of contravening ethical boundaries, has stood in the way of an open and responsible discussion on the use of touch in therapy. Touch in the Helping Professions is a welcome and much needed contribution to the field-a window onto a fundamental need. This book is published in English. - Cet ouvrage offre un ensemble de données probantes et de résultats cliniques à l'appui du toucher dans le développement physique et émotionnel. Il est structuré selon trois axes : la théorie sur le toucher; la pratique du toucher dans un contexte de thérapie, et les questions éthiques. Il aborde la question du rôle du genre, de l'âge, de la culture et de l'expérience de vie, des sujets comme la zoothérapie, la privation sensorielle, des objets sacrés, et des considérations d'ordre éthique. Les approches variées - philosophie, théologie, psychologie, anthropologie - remettent en question les présuppositions, offrent un contexte historico-culturelprofessionnel, et font appel à des données primaires.  Les collaborateurs soutiennent que le toucher sain et non sexuel n'est pas suffisamment enseigné dans le cadre de la formation professionnelle. Cette absence de dialogue - engendrée par la crainte de dépasser des bornes éthiques, fait en sorte qu'une discussion ouverte et responsable sur l'utilisation du toucher dans un cadre thérapeutique ne peut avoir lieu, alors même qu'elle contribuerait aux balises théoriques de notre compréhension de cet enjeu fondamental. Ce livre est publié en anglais.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Research & Methodology.2bisacsh  aHealth Care.  aHelping Professions.  aSocial Services.1 aBellehumeur, Christian R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerendsen, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBilodeau, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChambers, Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCharron, Natalie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Isaac, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDemasure, Karlijn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeist, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuindon, Marilyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuirguis-Younger, Manal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuirguis-Younger, Manal, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIsgandarova, Nazila, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLund, Kristine, eco